    '<span style="color: #076dad; font-weight:700;">Uncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">bind</span>to a site on the enzyme that is distinct from the <span style="color: #c80085; font-weight:700;">active site</span>.',
    '<span style="color: #3b7600; font-weight:700;">Noncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> affect<span style="color: #b74300; font-weight:700;">substrate</span> <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">binding</span>, but do NOT decrease catalysis.',
  ],
  [
    '<span style="color: #d40000; font-weight:700;">Competitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> only <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">bind</span>to the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span>.',
    '<span style="color: #d40000; font-weight:700;">Competitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">bind</span>to the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span> and prevent <span style="color: #007a00; font-weight:700;">product</span> formation.',
    '<span style="color: #d40000; font-weight:700;">Competitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> have a higher affinity for the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span> than for the free enzyme.',
    '<span style="color: #3b7600; font-weight:700;">Noncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> only <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">bind</span>to the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span>.',
    '<span style="color: #3b7600; font-weight:700;">Noncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> <span style="color: #a719db; font-weight:700;">bind</span>to the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span> and prevent <span style="color: #007a00; font-weight:700;">product</span> formation.',
    '<span style="color: #3b7600; font-weight:700;">Noncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> have a higher affinity for the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span> than for the free enzyme.',
    '<span style="color: #076dad; font-weight:700;">Uncompetitive&nbsp;inhibitors</span> have a higher affinity for the free enzyme than for the <span style="color: #6c6c00; font-weight:700;">enzyme-substrate complex</span>.',
  ],
  [
    '<span style="color: #935d00; font-weight:700;">Enzyme&nbsp;inhibitors</span> completely block all enzyme activity regardless of their concentration.',
